1. Z index is used to set elements on top of one another, but will only work if the position is set.

  &::before{
    content: "\201C";
    position: absolute;
    top: -2.75rem;
    left: -1rem;
    font-size: 20rem;
    color: var(--color-Grey-light-2);
    font-family: sans-serif;
    line-height: 1;
  }
  
    &__text{
    z-index: 10;
    position: relative;
  }
